5b89bed2353438664e000056.Title: Raspberry Pi (French)
5b89bed2353438664e000056.Lead:
On va aussi entreprendre une petite excursion dans le monde des capteurs et donner quelques astuces comment résoudre des problèmes types.

Après la partie théorique guidée du séminaire, vous êtes les bienvenus de rester et de travailler sur votre propre projet Raspberry Pi (17h - 20h). On sera là pour vous aider!
5b89bed2353438664e000056.Objectives:
- mettre en marche votre Raspberry Pi,
- se connecter à distance par SSH,
- connecter votre Pi à Internet via Wifi / Ethernet,
- lancer des programmes Python (et les faire tourner à infini),
- allumer et éteindre des périphériques en utilisant des relais.
5b89bed2353438664e000056.Ticket: Raspberry Pi 3: 35 CHF, Carte de relais: 10 CHF

5b8a6a943534383ffe000335.Title: Makers Night
5b8a6a943534383ffe000335.Lead: Do you have a project you want to bootstrap? Or are you curious to know more about our way of working or our projects? Maybe you hesitate to join the association? The Makers Night is the perfect opportunity to get to know us! We get together to advance on our projects, and update each other on our progress and the challenges we are facing.

5b8a6c50353438387a0000e9.Title: Pizza & LaTeX: Intro workshop to easy text editing
5b8a6c50353438387a0000e9.Lead:
Spend your time focusing on the content of your documents or slides, rather than on how to make them readable!

In this workshop, you will learn how to use LaTeX, a text editing system that allows you to easily typeset technical reports, linguistics papers, scientific articles, books, slides, posters...
5b8a6c50353438387a0000e9.Objectives:
- Key advantages of using LaTeX
- How to get started with LaTeX
- Introduction to key packages (graphics, tables, math tools, bibliography...)
- Best practices for using LaTeX: Customising, using different templates, structuring complex / long documents
- Guidelines for continuing the work

5b8a6da33534385ee20001d1.Title: PCB design in KiCAD for beginners
5b8a6da33534385ee20001d1.Lead:
When you open up and look into a computer, you see all these green boards with tiny components on them. Of course, these make that your computer can do all kinds of amazing things, like, displaying a movie on a screen.

But how are these made?! In this workshop you will learn!

Have you ever wanted to create your own custom electronic circuit? Then this workshop is for you! NO PRIOR KNOWLEDGE REQUIRED.

Bring your own laptop (Win/Mac/Linux)!
5b8a6da33534385ee20001d1.Objectives:
This theoretical part (13:30 - 17:00) will cover:
- Installation and Introduction to you to the free and open-source PCB design software ("KiCAD").
- Basics of electronic circuits design.
- Step-by-step guide to draw a simple circuit board with KiCAD.

After the theoretical part, you can stay here and design your own board. We will be here to help you (17:00 - 20:00)

5b8a6df235343860b20002c1.Title: Raspberry Pi Introduction Workshop
5b8a6df235343860b20002c1.Lead:
We'll also give an excursion into external sensors and some troubleshooting tips&tricks.

After the "theoretical part" of the workshop ends, you can stay and work on your Raspberry Pi project (16h -20h). We'll be there to help you.
5b8a6df235343860b20002c1.Objectives:
- power on your Raspberry Pi,
- remotely connect to your Raspberry Pi with SSH,
- connect to the internet using Wifi/Ethernet,
- run Python programs (and keeping them running forever),
- switch on/off external devices using a relay

5b8a6e4035343861020001ef.Title: 3d printing for EPFL students
5b8a6e4035343861020001ef.Objectives:
- How to get access to a 3d printer using an online booking tool
- How to create a model for 3d printing
- Best practices of printing
- Using other tools to finish off your print

5b8a6f2c35343861330001b8.Title: Design Thinking Workshop
5b8a6f2c35343861330001b8.Lead:
In this 90-minute meetup, we'll be hosting Standford's d.school Design Thinking crash course in groups of two.

No previous experience required.

You will start by interviewing your partner on a specific need (e.g. new wallet), then iterating on sketches and ending up with a quick and dirty prototype. Each phase is _strictly_ timeboxed and you will feel like we're not giving you enough time. This is normal, intended and you'll be able to

If you feel uncomfortable diving deep into your partners/clients/coworkers needs, if you don't like showing unfinished work and are often stuck over analyzing, if you don't know how to work with/give feedback, then this course might be for you! It changed how we work and think at Octanis and we want to spread the word.

We hope to see you for this super fast-paced and fun meetup! You'll be mostly drawing, talking, crafting and learning :)

5b8edc483534386dd40000f6.title: We have an old and broken scientific instrument. Want to help us repair it?
5b8edc483534386dd40000f6.content:
We've recently acquired a Scanning Electron Microscope (SEM). Unlike a regular microscope that works with visible light, a SEM works with an electron beam. This makes it possible to observe structures as small as a single molecule.

The SEM which we acquired is an analog model that dates from the 80ies. It weights roughly 300kg. Until recently, it was still perfectly functional. When it stopped working, its previous owner set it up for sale on the internet. When he noticed how motivated we were to repair the SEM, he gave it to us for free.

In this video Beat and Johannes explain how our SEM works - and what does not work!

But why would anyone want to spend time and energy repairing an old piece of scientific equipment? After all, a SEM is quite a complex tool, and nobody at Octanis has any experience with this type of project.

Working on this SEM means analysing and understanding a complex elecronic system. Such a skill is useful to anyone working in engineering. Debugging this SEM means learning how to solve various electronic problems in practice - on a system that is quite different from the ones typically shown in class. And that the SEM is old and analog is actually an advantage: All parts are discrete and can easily be replaced. All that is needed are basic tools - and quite some patience!

Starting such a project can be intimidating. Where to start? What if it doesn't work out? But rather than letting being paralysed by such questions, such a project should be seen as a valuable learning opportunity. When starting such a complex project, it is difficult to know whether we actually have the necessary skills - or what these skills are. But it is only by starting to work on it that it is possible to know which skills are needed, and it is only by keeping on working on the project that we can acquire these skills.

If you too would like to embark on this adventure, don't hesitate to join us for this project! No matter your specialisation, no matter whether you're a first year student or a professional - anybody can contribute to repairing the SEM.

Presentation of the project:

October 2, 19h, MED3 2215

Can't wait to learn more? Find the entire documentation here and a summary of the project here!
